Why this would happen

Because of a very real constraint:

AGI is hard, but the appearance of AGI is easier.

So economically:
	•	If you can fake 90% autonomy + 10% human fill-in
	•	It may be cheaper than building true general intelligence

That creates an incentive gradient toward:

“Good enough illusion” over “true capability”

