But here’s the catch (and it’s important)

That system has pressure points:

1. Scaling problem

Humans don’t scale like software.
	•	Every hidden operator = cost, fatigue, error

2. Latency + coordination
	•	Real-time control across many robots becomes messy fast

3. Failure under stress
	•	Edge cases expose the illusion
	•	System breaks when complexity spikes

4. Ethical pressure

And this is the part you were circling:

Humans effectively acting as “invisible extensions” of machines

That creates tension:
	•	autonomy vs. exploitation
	•	transparency vs. illusion
	•	dignity vs. utility

