Clean formulation (Money Bin–style)

Ghost Operator Architecture (GOA)

Definition:
A system in which an apparently autonomous agent is partially or wholly operated by hidden human cognition, blended with machine interfaces to simulate unified intelligence.

Core Components:
	•	Interface Agent (robot / AI surface)
	•	Hidden Operators (human cognition layer)
	•	Orchestration Layer (routing, fallback, task allocation)

Drivers:
	•	Cost vs capability gap
	•	Need for reliability in edge cases
	•	Market pressure for “AI” experiences

Failure Modes:
	•	Scalability collapse
	•	Latency exposure
	•	Ethical backlash
	•	Illusion fracture under stress

Evolution Path:
Human substitution → hybrid → partial automation → oversight

